author: Russell Brand
description:
Watching back the collapse of the Twin Towers and Building 7 with fresh eyes, the questions hit harder than ever. Was 9/11 really just as we were told—or was it the spark that exposed how crises become opportunities for the most powerful? From pulverized concrete and demolition-like footage to the profits of Big Pharma, Big Tech, and the military-industrial complex after both 9/11 and COVID, the pattern is clear: disaster leads to control. The real lesson isn’t in the rubble, but in how easily fear and chaos are weaponized to strip away freedom.
